1. cs.AI - The paper discusses the limitations of current AI approaches and proposes a new approach to problem-solving using category theory. 
2. cs.LO - The paper uses mathematical formalism to study the principles underlying general problem-solving capabilities. 
3. cs.DS - The paper focuses on problems that can be represented as tree-like structures, which is a common topic in data structures. 
4. cs.CC - The paper discusses the existence of equivalences across apparently unrelated problem domains, which is a common topic in computational complexity. 
5. cs.DM - The paper uses a metric on tree problems to quantify equivalences of problem categories, which is a common topic in data mining.
